\f0\fs36 \cf0 Add a challenge to the set.  There will be 2 set challenges. This will be the 2nd one.  The rest will be moved to a separate page called \'93other challenges\'94. \
\
This second challenge is called \'93This is not a drill.\'94 Create a page for it and Include a link to it in the overall workshop under the 2nd challenge. \
\
Here is intro text.  Use it mainly verbatim, but fact-check it and give me a proposed revision to approve or alter before you finalize and include it:\
\
<Start challenge text>\
A notice of major changes to NIH policy have just been published by the Office of Management and Budget.  The changes are described in the 108-page Federal Register, and would result in important changes to the grant-making process before and after the award of grants, which could have a profound impact on science in the U.S. and other countries to the degree to which they depend on NIH funding. \
\
The proposed changes are open for comment until July 13. The U.S. government is required to consider substantive comments. Your task is to use AI to help understand the proposed changes and craft a response. Some types of comments will have more impact than others. Write a comment that is designed to align with your values and be impactful, i.e., considered by OMB. AI can be helpful here, but you are the ones who must understand the issues at stake, and form an opinion. Here is a link:\
\
https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/05/29/2026-10817/regulation-for-federal-financial-assistance#footnote-8-p32200\
\
Consider breaking down the task into components.\
\
Context:\
Why are these changes being proposed?\
Content:\
What are the most important changes?\
Impact: \
What will the impact be on science, scientists, and other stakeholders? e.g., study-section functioning, awards, recruitment, trainees, clinical trials, publication compliance, collaborations, indirect-cost administration, or institutional operations.\
Reponse:\
What kinds of comments is OMB obligated to consider? What will make a comment likely to be considered as a substantive comment?\
Action plan:\
How can you submit your comment?\
\
